We recommended and the Management agreed to:

Direct the Acting Municipal Accountant to draw journal entries to correct the discrepancy of ₱1,000.00 and to exclude one parcel of land amounting to ₱6.049 million plus the additional five lots discovered with Certificates of Title that were not in the name of the Municipality from its assets to reflect the correct balance of the Land account in the FS;

Direct the Acting Municipal Accountant to be cautious in the drawing of entries in recognizing the amounts to be taken up in the books to avoid erroneous recording so that the financial statements are fairly presented; 

Make sure that only assets of the Municipality are reported in the financial statements.

We recommended and the management agreed that the Acting Municipal Accountant to: 

Prepare properly the BRS for all accounts maintained by the Municipality with complete supporting documents;

Exhaust all means to retrieve the necessary data/documents for immediate adjustments in the books of account of all identified reconciling items

Recommendations
We recommended and the management agreed to:
Require the Inventory Committee to prepare and submit the RCPPE using the prescribed format;
Ensure that the Inventory Committee, the GSO and the Accounting Office reconcile all the inventory reports for proper presentation in the Financial Statements;
Ensure that the GSO maintains complete PCs by providing identification number, issued quantity, acknowledgement receipt for equipment (ARE) and stickers for each property; and
Ensure that the Accounting Office maintains PPELCs and update them periodically to aid in the conduct of Physical Inventory Count and in the reconciliation of balances between the Inventory Report and the books of accounts.

Recommendations
We recommended and the management agreed to:
Designate a responsible official to facilitate the processing of the Certificate of Title of the 17 parcels of land owned by the Municipality in order to establish absolute ownership and protect the interest of the Municipality over these properties;
Create an Appraisal Committee composed of the Municipal Assessor, Engineer, Acting Accountant and Treasurer to facilitate the appraisal of the value of the parcels of land owned by the Municipality;
Direct the Acting Municipal Accountant to recognize in the books of account the unrecorded land properties of the Municipality;
Direct the Acting Municipal Accountant to maintain Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards for the land account; and
Direct the General Services Officer to maintain Property Cards for the parcels of land and other real properties owned by the Municipality.

Recommendations
We recommended and the management agreed to:
Direct the Acting Municipal Accountant to comply with the reportorial requirements and submit the lacking supporting documents to rectify the deficiencies noted;
Direct the Acting Municipal Accountant to properly verify the payments to avoid error in computations and make sure that it shall not exceed the rate per day of the job hires;
Implement a one DTR per month for all the employees and job hires of the Municipality; and
Direct the refund of the excess payment in the payroll.
